Dax Functions:

1207head

YEAR(Date) 				- Returns the year of a date as a four digit integer.
MONTH(Date) 				- Returns a number from 1 (January) to 12 (December) representing the month.
YEAR(Date) 				- Returns the year of a date as a four digit integer.

WEEKDAY(Date, [ReturnType]) 		- Returns a number from 1 to 7 identifying the day of the week of a date.
WEEKNUM(Date, [ReturnType]) 		- Returns the week number in the year.

FORMAT(Value, Format, [LocaleName]) 	- Converts a value to text in the specified number format.

Sort by column Step
- to sort month use MONTH( ), to sort week use WEEKDAY( )


1207tail

Column = YEAR([SalesDate])
Column = MONTH([SalesDate])
Column = DAY([SalesDate])

Column = [Sales] - [Profit]
Column = [Sales] + [Profit]
Column = [Sales] * [Profit]
Column = [Sales] / [Profit]

Column = WEEKNUM([SalesDate])
Column = WEEKDAY([SalesDate])

Column = FORMAT([SalesDate], "MMMM")
Column = FORMAT([SalesDate], "MMM")
Column = FORMAT([SalesDate], "DDDD")
Column = FORMAT([SalesDate], "DDD")





